element.text: Contain proteins that are essential for virion structure and immune system modulation, for example inhibiting the host oxidative response.
Proteins on the outside of the membrane that attach to host cell receptors for entry
Lipid membrane that fuses with host membrane on cell entry and release
Paracrystalline layer that surrounds and protects the monkeypox core
Double stranded DNA and protein complex. In the core there are proteins such as DNA polymerase that enable replication
